            "map_keywords": [
              "Mojácar Pueblo",
              "Plaza Nueva Mojácar",
              "Mirador del Castillo Mojácar",
              "Fuente Mora Mojácar",
              "Iglesia Santa María Mojácar",
              "Puerta de la Ciudad Mojácar",
              "Mojácar Playa"
            ]
          },
          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "Mojácar Pueblo perches at 170 meters altitude at the end of the Sierra Cabrera. Its maze of whitewashed alleys preserves the village's Al-Andalus structure. On the facades, the Indalo—a Neolithic cave figure from the Cueva de los Letreros—is painted on doors to ward off the evil eye.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            },
            {
              "text": "The Mirador del Castillo, built on the ruins of a 16th-century castle, offers 360-degree views: the sea, the Río Aguas valley, and the Sierra Cabrera mountains. Come at sunset for the best light.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 30
            },
            {
              "text": "The Fuente Mora is where, according to tradition, Mojácar's last Moorish governor negotiated peaceful surrender to the Catholic Monarchs in 1488. Its twelve water jets flow beneath a commemorative plaque.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 20
            },
            {
              "text": "The Church of Santa María, built around 1560 on the site of a former mosque, retains a fortress-like appearance. At its feet, the arcade-bordered Plaza del Parterre serves as a terrace with valley views.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 30
            },
            {
              "text": "Pass through the Puerta de la Ciudad, a 16th-century entrance gate adorned with Mojácar's emblem: a double-headed eagle. Just inside, the Casa del Torreón served as a customs house where visitors paid to enter the village.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 20
            },
            {
              "text": "Descend to Mojácar Playa for its 17 km of coastline. Among the beaches, Marina de la Torre and El Descargador fly the blue flag. Fine sand and calm waters make them family-friendly beaches.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 60
            }
          ],
          "activities": [
            {
              "text": "Get lost in the flower-filled alleys of Mojácar Pueblo. Purple bougainvillea spills from white balconies, and every corner reveals a new sea view.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 60
            },
            {
              "text": "Olive oil and roasted almond tasting in the village's grocery shops. Almería province produces renowned extra virgin olive oil from Picual and Arbequina olives.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 45
            },
            {
              "text": "Grilled fish dinner on the Mojácar Playa waterfront. The espeto—sardines grilled on wood-fire skewers—is a local specialty.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 75
            }
          ],
