          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "From Granada, expect about an hour's drive to reach Lanjarón, the gateway to the Alpujarras. This small spa town is famous for its mineral water (Spain's best-selling brand) and its ruined Arab castle, the last Moorish stronghold to fall in 1500. Make a quick stop to refill your water bottle at one of the public fountains and grab a coffee on the plaza before continuing.",
