          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "You're leaving Andalusia for the Murcia region. Caravaca de la Cruz is the fifth holy city of Christianity, along with Jerusalem, Rome, Santiago de Compostela and Santo Toribio de Liébana. This privilege, granted by Pope John Paul II in 1998, allows a perpetual Jubilee to be celebrated every seven years. Everything revolves around the Vera Cruz, a reliquary containing fragments of Christ's cross. According to legend, in 1231, the Moorish king Abou Zeïd asked a captive priest to celebrate mass in the castle. Since a cross was missing, two angels brought one from heaven - and the Moorish king converted to Christianity.",
