              "text": "Head west (2h30) to reach Sos del Rey Católico, in the Cinco Villas comarca. Perched on a rocky promontory on the border between the ancient kingdoms of Aragón and Navarre, this fortified city witnessed the birth on March 10, 1452 of one of the most important figures in Spanish history: Ferdinand II of Aragón, the Catholic King, who, together with Isabella of Castile, unified Spain and financed Christopher Columbus's voyage. The village, classified as a Historic Site since 1968, is one of Aragón's best preserved - seven fortified gates still pierce the Gothic ramparts.",
