              "text": "Continue 30 minutes east to reach Valderrobres, capital of the Matarraña comarca, nicknamed 'Aragonese Tuscany.' The arrival is spectacular: the medieval stone bridge spans the Río Matarraña and leads straight to the San Roque gate, one of seven gates in the old wall. At the village summit, the archbishop's castle-palace (14th-15th centuries) connects to the church of Santa María la Mayor, one of Aragón's finest examples of Levantine Gothic. Its sculpted facade and rose window are remarkably delicate.",
