          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "The Basilica del Pilar, Spain's largest baroque sanctuary, stretches 130 meters along the Ebro riverbank. Its eleven domes and four towers dominate the Plaza del Pilar. Inside, two cupolas bear frescoes by the young Goya, a native of the region: the Adoration of the Name of God and Regina Martyrum.",
              "place_id": "",
