            {
              "text": "Take the elevator to the top of the Pilar tower, 62 meters high: the panorama sweeps across Zaragoza's rooftops, the ribbon of the Ebro, and distant mountain ranges. Below, the Holy Chapel houses the jasper column where the Virgin is said to have appeared to the apostle James in the year 40 AD.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 30
