          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "The Torre del Salvador, soaring 40 meters high, is the jewel of Teruel's Mudéjar architecture. Its bands of brick and white-and-green azulejo tiles form geometric patterns of remarkable precision. Climb its 122 steps: the interpretation center inside explains Mudéjar masons' techniques, and the summit offers a panorama across the entire city.",
