            {
              "text": "The Mausoleum of the Lovers of Teruel houses the remains of Isabel de Segura and Juan Martínez de Marcilla, Spain's \"Romeo and Juliet.\" Their alabaster effigies, sculpted by Juan de Ávalos, face each other without touching. The adjacent 14th-century Church of San Pedro features a richly decorated interior in Aragonese Mudéjar style.",
              "place_id": "",
