            {
              "text": "The Cathedral of Santa María de Mediavilla is worth visiting especially for its 1257 Mudéjar bell tower, Teruel's oldest, and its extraordinary painted wooden coffered ceiling from around 1300. This Gothic-Mudéjar ceiling blends everyday scenes, hunting and war imagery with fantastic animals, in a unique fusion of Islamic and Christian traditions.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 40
            },
            {
              "text": "The Escalinata, a monumental neo-Mudéjar staircase from the early 20th century, connects the train station to the city center. Its bricks, ceramics, and wrought iron echo the motifs of medieval towers. At the top, the Torre del Salvador appears in visual alignment, creating a striking perspective.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 20
            },
            {
              "text": "The Plaza del Torico, Teruel's beating heart, takes its name from the small bull statue perched on a column at the center of the fountain. The surrounding arcades and colorful balconies make it the natural gathering point for a terrace break.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 20
