              "text": "Albarracín appears around a bend in the Guadalaviar, clinging to a rose sandstone cliff at 1,100 meters elevation. Declared a National Monument in 1961, this village of 1,000 inhabitants is considered one of Spain's most beautiful. Its facades of reddish rodeno sandstone and wooden balconies create a fairytale medieval atmosphere.",
