              "text": "Albarracín's ramparts extend across an area far larger than the village itself. Three construction phases can be read in the stone: the 10th-century bastion and Torre del Andador, the 11th-century walls of the Berber taifa of Banu Razin, then Christian fortifications after the Reconquest. From atop the Torre del Andador, the panorama embraces the entire valley.",
