              "text": "The church and cloister of San Pedro el Viejo, a national monument since 1885, form one of Aragon's most important Romanesque ensembles. The 1149 cloister preserves 18 original capitals sculpted by the Master of San Juan de la Peña, depicting the life of Christ. The Chapel of San Bartolomé houses the royal pantheon of kings Alfonso I the Battler and Ramiro II the Monk.",
