              "text": "Facing the cathedral, the Town Hall occupies a 16th-century Renaissance palace. This is where the bloody legend of the \"Bell of Huesca\" allegedly occurred: King Ramiro II supposedly beheaded rebellious nobles and arranged their heads in the shape of a bell to impose his authority.",
