            {
              "text": "The Provincial Museum of Huesca, housed in the 16th-century Casa de la Comunidad, displays a Roman archaeological section, a reconstructed old pharmacy, and, on the top floor, very fine ceramics from the Al-Andalus period. The terrace offers a view over the city's rooftops.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 35
