          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "The Charco de San Ginés defines Arrecife: a natural seawater lagoon in the heart of the capital, lined with whitewashed fishermen's houses. This natural harbor has existed for over six centuries—the city was born here after the Franco-Norman conquest in the 15th century. César Manrique redesigned it as a serene promenade. Walk its perimeter in early morning when the light is soft and the terraces still quiet.",
