              "text": "Lunch around Charco de San Ginés: the area brims with restaurants serving Canarian classics—papas arrugadas with mojo verde or mojo rojo, fresh fish from the port, and malvasía wines from the island. It's also the best spot to watch fishing boats maneuver through the lagoon.",
