              "text": "At Islote de Hilario, don't miss the geothermal demonstrations: staff thrust brushwood into a simple hole in the ground—it ignites within seconds. Then a bucket of water poured into a pipe erupts in a geyser of boiling steam, because the earth's crust is only two meters thick here and temperatures exceed 400°C below. At 27 meters depth, near the main crater, the thermometer reads 700°C. Since 2013, NASA astronauts have trained in this park—the basaltic soil geologically resembles Mars.",
