              "activity_duration_min": 360,
              "practical_info": {
                "duration": "~6h",
                "difficulty": "Demanding"
              }
            },
            {
              "text": "Stargazing from La Palma's heights. The island obtained UNESCO's first Starlight Reserve status worldwide in 2011—no light pollution, perfectly stable skies. Roque de los Muchachos (2,426 m), the island's summit, houses one of the world's most important astronomical observatories. Outside observatory visiting hours, the mountain roads are freely accessible for night observation.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 90
