            {
              "text": "Los Llanos de Aridane is La Palma's most populous town, set in the green Aridane valley on the western slope—a microclimate warmer and sunnier than the capital's. The historic center houses the Museum of the Street, a permanent outdoor contemporary art exhibition unique in Europe: since 1999, murals painted directly on the city's blank facades by recognized artists cover up to 140 m² of walls. Wander the alleys to find them.",
