            {
              "text": "Tajogaite volcano—also called Cumbre Vieja—erupted on September 19, 2021 and flowed for 85 days until December. The flow covered 1,218 hectares, destroyed 1,345 houses and 73 km of roads, and expanded the island by 47 hectares into the sea. From Los Llanos, Mirador de Tajuya offers the best view of the entire lava field and the new volcanic cone. Guided 5 km trails allow you to approach the crater's base from Llano del Jable.",
