          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "The castle of Peñíscola has dominated the rocky promontory since 1307. Built by the Knights Templar atop an Arab alcazaba, it became the palace of Pope Benedict XIII—Papa Luna—after 1411.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 90
            },
            {
              "text": "Step through the Portal de San Pedro to enter the old town. Cobbled lanes climb between whitewashed facades all the way up to the castle's parade ground.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 75
            },
            {
              "text": "Renaissance ramparts wrap around the peninsula for 2 kilometers. From the muralla del Olvido, you can take in the entire coastline and the old town spread out below.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 60
            },
            {
              "text": "The church of Santa María occupies a former mosque converted in the 14th century. Its bell tower has served as a landmark for sailors for centuries.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 45
            },
            {
              "text": "The Casa de las Conchas boasts a facade entirely covered in seashells—a unique decoration commissioned by a local family in the 19th century.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 30
            },
            {
              "text": "Walk out to the lighthouse built in 1899, still keeping watch over the Mediterranean horizon. The surrounding maritime garden offers a cool refuge from the sun.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 30
            },
            {
              "text": "The Artillery Park spreads out at the foot of the castle. Its terraced gardens host bird-of-prey shows and provide access to the underground casemates.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 45
            }
          ],
          "activities": [
            {
              "text": "Playa Norte stretches for 2 kilometers of fine sand. Its calm waters are perfect for swimming with views of the castle perched above.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 90
            },
            {
              "text": "Rice with cuttlefish stains the dish a deep black. This emblematic specialty is best savored at restaurants along the harbor or the seafront promenade.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 75
            },
            {
              "text": "Find a spot on the rocks as the day draws to a close. The sun drops behind the castle while lights begin to flicker on throughout the old town.",
