              "text": "The Almacén de los Fúcares—the Fuggers' warehouse—is an imposing 16th-century building that served as a grain store and mercury warehouse for the Augsburg bankers. These financiers were so powerful they lent money to Charles V in exchange for the Almadén mercury monopoly. The building, sometimes called a palace because its construction is so refined, now hosts exhibitions. Just next door, the Church of San Agustín, declared of Cultural Interest, deserves a look for its Renaissance cloister.",
