              "text": "Twenty-five minutes' drive east from Medinaceli brings you to the Monastery of Santa María de Huerta, one of Spain's most beautiful Cistercian monasteries. Founded in 1162, expropriated in 1835 during the Mendizábal disentailment, then returned to the order in 1930, it's still home to some twenty monks. Push through the door and you enter eight centuries of silence. The Gothic cloister (13th century), with its pointed arcades and austere garden, prepares you for the shock of the refectory—an immense hall covered with sexpartite rib vaults, pierced by tall windows that flood the space with light. It's one of Europe's most beautiful monastic refectories.",
