              "text": "Brihuega is nicknamed the \"Garden of Alcarria\"—and in July, \"Spanish Provence.\" This fortified medieval village, declared a historic ensemble in 1973, overlooks the Tajuña valley from its hill. Begin with the 12th-century ramparts, nearly two kilometers long, pierced by monumental gates: the Puerta de la Cadena, Puerta del Juego de Pelota, and Arco de Cozagón. The Castillo de la Piedra Bermeja, south of the village, dates from the same era and offers a panoramic view over the surrounding fields.",
