              "text": "The Sagrada Família tells the story of a construction begun in 1882 and still unfinished - making it the world's largest incomplete Catholic church. Gaudí took over the project in 1883 and devoted the final 43 years of his life to it. In October 2025, the central tower reached 162 meters, finally surpassing Montjuïc mountain by just one meter - Gaudí believed no human creation should exceed nature. Book your tickets online well in advance, even off-season: 4.5 million visitors flock here annually.",
