              "text": "Just steps away, Passeig de Gràcia showcases Gaudí's two wildest houses. Casa Batlló, renovated between 1904 and 1906, is nicknamed the 'house of bones' - its limestone pillars evoke skeletons and its balconies, skulls. Casa Milà (La Pedrera), built between 1906 and 1912, was the last house Gaudí designed before dedicating himself entirely to the Sagrada Família. Its rooftop, with twisted chimneys, offers one of the city's finest vantage points - the classic spot for photographing the Sagrada Família through the arches.",
