              "Paseo del Espolón Burgos",
              "Museo Evolución Humana Burgos",
              "Monasterio de las Huelgas Burgos"
            ]
          },
          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "Burgos Cathedral is the only religious building in Spain inscribed on the UNESCO World Heritage list independently. The first stone was laid by Ferdinand III and Bishop Mauricio on July 20, 1221; construction stretched until 1765, summarizing in itself the entire history of Spanish Gothic. Its 84-meter towers topped with openwork spires from the 15th century dominate the old town for miles. Inside, look for the tomb of El Cid and his wife Doña Jimena beneath the central lantern tower. Don't miss the Chapel of the Constables (Capilla del Condestable), a masterpiece of late Gothic, or the Papamoscas that chimes the hours from a balcony between two bells. Arrive late afternoon from Astorga: the illuminated cathedral at dusk is a spectacle in itself. Book tickets online.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 90
            },
            {
              "text": "The next morning before leaving Burgos, don't miss the Cartuja de Miraflores, 3 km from the center. This 15th-century Gothic monastery houses the polychrome tomb of the parents of the Catholic Monarchs—John II and Isabella of Portugal—sculpted by Gil de Siloé. It's one of the summits of Spanish Gothic sculpture. Entry is free. From the forecourt, the Arco de Santa María and the Paseo del Espolón along the Arlanzón River offer a beautiful transitional walk before the drive to Orbaneja.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 60
            }
          ],
          "activities": [
            {
              "text": "The Museum of Human Evolution is directly linked to excavations at the Atapuerca site, 15 km from Burgos, where the oldest human remains in Western Europe were discovered—Homo antecessor, approximately 800,000 years old. The original collections and reconstructions make for a fascinating half-day even for non-specialists. If time is tight, prioritize the cathedral on arrival evening and the Cartuja on departure morning.",
              "place_id": "",
              "activity_duration_min": 120
            }
