              "text": "Ledesma is built on a rocky spur between two meanders of the Tormes—a naturally defensive position inhabited since prehistoric times. The Romans called it Bletisama in honor of Consul Bleto (93 AD). Medieval repopulation dates to 1161, when Fernando II raised the walls and fortress. In 1462, Enrique IV handed lordship of Ledesma to Don Beltrán de la Cueva, his favorite, who made it a city of splendor in the 15th century. Classified as a historic site in 1975, Ledesma preserves fragments of Roman and medieval wall.",
