              "text": "The Puente de los Franceses (Bridge of the French) spans the Águeda River below the village—the only crossing point of the Arribes de l'Águeda. According to tradition, it was built by Gauls settled in the region, whose name may be the origin of 'Gallegos' in the village name. The descent to the bridge crosses steep slopes of the riverbank with dense Mediterranean vegetation (olive trees, cork oaks) characteristic of the Arribes microclimate.",
