          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "En route south, cross through Monfragüe National Park, one of Europe's top raptor-watching sites. Stop at the Salto del Gitano viewpoint: from this lookout above the Tajo River, you'll observe—almost guaranteed—griffon vultures gliding above their cliff-nesting colonies, black storks, Spanish imperial eagles, and sometimes black vultures. During breeding season (February–June), the spectacle is guaranteed. Allow 1 hour for the viewpoint, more if you climb to Monfragüe castle for 360° views over the dehesas.",
