            {
              "text": "Arrive in Cáceres late afternoon. If you haven't yet seen the Ciudad Monumental (UNESCO since 1986), treat yourself to at least a twilight stroll through its lanes—when day-trippers have left and the golden-stone Renaissance palaces light up. Plaza de Santa María, the Bujaco tower, and the Palacio de los Golfines de Abajo deserve a look even in passing. If you've already visited Cáceres, simply enjoy the evening on a Plaza Mayor terrace.",
