          "visits": [
            {
              "text": "Mérida is the ancient Augusta Emerita, capital of the Roman province of Lusitania founded in 25 BC, and one of the best-preserved Roman sites outside Italy (UNESCO since 1993). If you haven't visited yet, absolutely don't miss the Roman theatre—built between 16 and 15 BC, it still hosts a classical theatre festival every summer. Its scaenae frons with Corinthian columns, 17 meters high, is one of the most spectacular in the Roman Empire. Right next door, the amphitheatre (8 BC, 15,000 seats) completes the picture.",
