              "text": "Cross the Puente Romano over the Guadiana—792 meters long, 60 arches, one of the longest Roman bridges still standing. The crossing is pedestrian and offers beautiful views over the city and Arab Alcazaba at twilight. If you've already seen Mérida, simply pass through town and enjoy the evening dining near the Temple of Diana.",
