              "visit_duration_min": 45
            },
            {
              "text": "Walk up to the Cathedral of San Martín, a national monument begun in the 12th century. Its hidden treasure is the Pórtico del Paraíso (Paradise Portico), a polychrome Romanesque sculptural ensemble that has retained its original colours—an exceptionally rare thing. It's the 'cousin' of Santiago's famous Pórtico de la Gloria, but here the medieval paintwork remains intact. In the Chapel of San Cosme and San Damián, there's a quirky feature: a permanent nativity scene displayed all year round, with figures dressed in Galician costume. Exit via the Praza Maior, surrounded by arcades, where you'll find the Casa Consistorial and the archaeological museum housed in the old episcopal palace.",
              "place_id": "",
              "visit_duration_min": 60
