            {
              "text": "Descend towards the Miño through the old town—medieval lanes, Renaissance palaces, shady squares. The Ponte Vella (Old Bridge), of Roman origin but rebuilt in the 13th century, spans the river on seven stone arches. On the far side, the ultra-modern Ponte do Milenio (2001) creates a spectacular contrast with its millennial neighbour.",
