              "text": "First stop: Celanova, 30 minutes south of Ourense. The Monastery of San Salvador, founded in 936 by San Rosendo (a Galician bishop and saint), is one of the most important in Galicia. The church, rebuilt in Baroque style in the 17th–18th centuries, impresses with its monumental façade and regular cloister. But Celanova's true treasure hides behind the monastery: the Chapel of San Miguel, a tiny 10th-century Mozarabic oratory, one of the few pre-Romanesque buildings in all of Galicia. Its horseshoe arches and miniature proportions transport you to an era when Christians and Muslims shared a common architectural vocabulary.",
