            {
              "text": "On Plaza Mayor, facing the cathedral, don't miss Casa de los Picos—\"House of Spikes\"—a Renaissance façade bristling with 617 diamond-cut granite points, designed by the Marquises of Quintanar in the late 15th century. Calle Juan Bravo concentrates Segovia's finest façades: Renaissance sgraffito with geometric motifs, noble palaces, Casa de la Tierra, Torreón de Lozoya. Five minutes on foot between all these points. Everything in Segovia fits within two kilometers.",
