            {
              "text": "Outside the walls, five minutes on foot from Puerta del Alcázar, the Basilica of San Vicente is one of Spain's finest Romanesque buildings. Built between the 11th and 13th centuries on the site where saints Vincent, Sabina, and Christeta were allegedly martyred in 304 under Diocletian. The stone tomb-cenotaph at the nave's center recounts their martyrdom in moving sculpted bas-reliefs: flagellation, torture, embalming by a converted Jewish lady. West façade with its grand portico, historiated capitals, golden light in the morning. A stop on the Camino del Sur.",
