              "text": "Salamanca has two adjoining cathedrals, the only one in Spain. The Old Cathedral, from the 12th century, Romanesque, preserves in its apse an altarpiece of 53 panels painted by Nicolás Florentino around 1445—one of Spain's largest Gothic ensembles, topped by a fresco of the Last Judgment. The New Cathedral, late Gothic then baroque, was begun in 1513 without destroying the old one—which is rare. Curiosity: on the north façade (Ramos door), an astronaut and a faun eating ice cream were carved in 1992 during restoration. Look closely.",
