              "text": "Tapas crawl in Calle Van Dyck or around Plaza Mayor. Salamanca is one of Spain's tapa capitals—here it's still offered with your drink, unlike Madrid or Barcelona. Try the hornazo (pâté of meat, serrano ham, chorizo and hard-boiled egg), chanfaina (ratatouille with rice and beef tongue), and especially Guijuelo ibérico ham, 30 km from Salamanca—one of Spain's best PDOs, raised on acorns in the oak groves of the Sierra de Béjar.",
