              "text": "The Convent of San Esteban, ten minutes from Plaza Mayor, is one of Salamanca's finest Plateresque buildings—a 30-meter-high façade-altarpiece in stone carved by Juan de Ribero between 1524 and 1610, with a relief scene of Saint Stephen's Stoning. A Dominican convent where Christopher Columbus stayed in 1486 during negotiations with university theologians. The main altarpiece by José de Churriguera (1693) is a 27-meter-high baroque explosion. The Renaissance cloister, by Juan de Álava, is a haven of calm.",
