              "text": "Right next door, the Convent of Las Dueñas has an absolutely unique hexagonal cloister—there's no other in Spain with this shape. Built in the 16th century for Dominican nuns, it's still inhabited by 9 cloistered sisters who sell pastries via a rotating turnstile (you speak through the wall, put money in the turntable, it rotates, cookies arrive). Especially: the cloister capitals. Grotesque sculptures, demons, monsters, rare for a convent—scholars still disagree on their meaning.",
