              "text": "Casa Lis, above the Tormes against the old walls, houses the Museum of Art Nouveau and Art Deco, one of Spain's best. The house itself, built in 1905 by modernist Joaquín de Vargas, is a marvel—multicolored stained glass flooding the hall, floral ironwork, marble and bronze staircase. Collection: 19,000 pieces including porcelain dolls by Bru and Jumeau, bronzes by Demêtre Chiparus, Émile Gallé furniture. Very intimate visit, never crowded.",
