            {
              "text": "Zamora is nicknamed \"the pearl of the Duero\" and \"the city of Romanesque art.\" With 24 Romanesque churches from the 12th-13th centuries, it's the world's greatest urban concentration of Romanesque. The cathedral, founded by Alfonso VII, consecrated in 1175 after 25 years of construction, is a unique blend of Romanesque, Byzantine, and Herreran. Its lantern tower—the cimborio—is its signature piece: a 16-sided dome covered with stone scales like a Japanese mushroom, inspired by Constantinople's Hagia Sophia via the Crusaders. Don't miss the Bishop's Door, one of Spain's finest Romanesque portals.",
