              "text": "The cathedral museum preserves one of the world's most important collections of Flemish tapestries—12 pieces from the 15th and 16th centuries, workshops of Arras, Tournai, and Brussels. The Trojan War series (1480), 4 by 7 meters each, recounts the fate of Hector and Achilles with a thousand figures embroidered in gold thread. Acquired by Zamoran bishops at mind-boggling prices, they survived the Napoleonic Wars and the Civil War. It's the textile equivalent of the Sistine Chapel—and nobody queues here.",
