              "text": "Valladolid, final stop. 300,000 inhabitants, capital of Castile-León, but a city often underestimated. Yet: Spain's capital under Philip II and Philip III (1601-1606), place where Cervantes published the first edition of Don Quixote in 1605, city where Christopher Columbus died in 1506, and site of the Catholic Monarchs' marriage in 1469. Plaza Mayor (1561), rebuilt after the same year's fire, is one of Spain's oldest enclosed plazas mayores and served as model for Madrid and Salamanca. Red façades, white arcades, lively square.",
