            {
              "text": "Tarragona Cathedral, perched at the city's highest point, sits atop the foundations of a Roman temple dedicated to Augustus. Construction began around 1171 under Archbishop Bernat Tort and continued until 1331, straddling late Romanesque (west facade with 12th-century portals) and Gothic (nave rising 26 meters high, stretching 104 meters long). The main altarpiece in polychrome alabaster by Pere Johan (15th century) is a jewel of Catalan Gothic sculpture. The Gothic rose window, measuring 10.50 meters in diameter, is Catalonia's largest. Admission €11, cloister access included. Remarkable acoustics during Sunday masses.",
