              "text": "The Museu Nacional Arqueològic de Tarragona houses the finest pieces excavated from Tarraco: the fish mosaic (47 marine species depicted in the 3rd century, discovered in 1955 at the Roman villa of Cal·lípolis in Vila-seca, measuring 6.25 × 4.50 meters), the colossal head of Augustus, and early Christian sarcophagi. The building itself, constructed in 1844, is Spain's oldest archaeological museum. Closed for renovation until 2027; temporary exhibitions at Tinglado 4 in the port - verify before visiting. When it reopens, allow 1.5 hours.",
