            {
              "text": "The Centcelles Mausoleum, 7 km from Tarragona in the village of Constantí, is southern Catalonia's most mysterious artifact: a 4th-century Roman tomb whose 11-meter dome bears one of the world's oldest Christian mosaics - discovered in 1877. Scenes from the Old Testament, hunts, seasons, with quality comparable to those in Ravenna. Whose tomb was it? The leading hypothesis, defended by the German Archaeological Institute, identifies Emperor Constans I, son of Constantine the Great, assassinated in Hispania in 350. Others see an ecclesiastical dignitary or local aristocrat. Guided tour required, €4, limited time slots, reservation recommended.",
