              "text": "The Cathedral of Santa Maria is the only entirely Romanesque cathedral preserved in Catalonia - reason enough to come. Begun around 1116, completed in 1175 by a certain Ramon Lambard, probably Italian: this explains the unusual Lombard arcading on the facade, unique in the region. Local peculiarity: the Bishop of Urgell has been, since the 13th century, one of the two co-princes of Andorra, the other being the French president. Combined ticket with the cloister and museum: €7. Allow 90 minutes for the complete tour.",
