              "text": "The Guggenheim Bilbao, opened in 1997 on the banks of the Nervión, literally saved a city in industrial decline. 24,000 m² of titanium, limestone and glass designed by Frank Gehry - and a permanent collection that holds its own, from Richard Serra to Jeff Koons. If you only have 2 hours, head straight for the Serra room: the Torqued Ellipses sculptures stand 4 meters tall and swallow you whole. Entry around €18, free Tuesday evenings after 6pm.",
