              "text": "The crossing of the Sierra de Cantabria from Bilbao is a tipping point you won't forget. In 20 minutes of climbing, the green, humid Atlantic landscape brutally gives way to the Ebro plain: vineyards as far as the eye can see, drier sky, different light. It's the curtain dropping on Rioja. Stop at the pass to take in the amplitude - on clear days, you can spot Logroño 60 km away.",
