              "text": "Founded in 1858, Marqués de Riscal is one of the first houses to have imported Bordeaux techniques to Rioja. But frankly, people come mainly for the architectural shock: the hotel designed by Frank Gehry in 2006 sits on the vineyards like a sculpture of pink and gold titanium that landed there by mistake. €75 million invested, and it shows. The cellar tour (2h, €30-40) covers the history, the wine cellars and a tasting. The Reserva remains the benchmark cuvée; for larger budgets, the Gran Reserva.",
