              "text": "The railway station's architecture astonishes: closer to a Belle Époque palace than a utilitarian station, the Estació del Nord was inaugurated in 1917 with Valencian ceramic frescoes on every wall. It still functions—travellers await their trains surrounded by orange-tree mosaics.",
